Deputy President William Ruto remained on his charm offensive, assuring of the governments support for the controversial gender equity bill that was deferred on Wednesday. Speaking during several functions across the country, the deputy president urged women  not  to relent until the bill sails through. He spoke as  a section of Ford Kenya leaders who accompanied him at the homecoming of Kimilili MPs Didmus Baraza in Bungoma dared their ODM counterparts of the sharing of political funds.   